  "title": "An Experimental Empire",
  "article_text": "In a distant land, an experimental empire was built by a gentle ruler. The institutional changes were slow but functional, and attendance at public meetings became voluntary. A stranger wandered into the city and took a slice of bread from a pale stall. The bread had an organic taste, and a dark stain on the cloth caught his eye. Subsequently, the ownership of the land was suspended by the king. The athlete's tongue was sharp, but his qualification for the race was clear. The server brought a cup of tea, and the shade of a tree offered cool rest. The grain in the fields grew tall, and the structural design of the buildings was strong. It is the empire that will fall if the ruler should become weak. Never had such a pale and gentle leader been seen before.",
